bol vett osszeallitassal kovetjuk a pillanatrol-pillanatra elesedo valsagot]* HORN NYILATKOZATHorn Gyula miniszterelnok nyilatkozata a szombati Nepszabadsagban a kozponti nyomozohivatalrol [teljes szoveg, betu szerint]Horn Gyula miniszterelnok a kozponti nyomozohivatal tervezett letrehozasaval kapcsolatos csutortoki, sikertelen kormanyules utan tegnap nyilatkozatot tett kozze. Az alabbiakban teljes terjedelmeben kozoljuk a miniszterelnok allasfoglalasat. [Maga a "nyilatkozat" tenye jelzi, hogy Horn ez alkalommal "rendithetetlenul" elszant a "High Noon"-szeru kenyertoresre. Ebbol a nyilatkozatbol visszalepni nem lehet, csak Horn teljes osszeomlasaval. Na nezzuk csak, mit is uzen, kinek] Az orszag kormanyzasaban vallalt felelossegembol kiindulva vilagossa kivanom tenni a hazai es a nemzetkozi kozvelemeny elott: [Hoppa, ez a "nemzetkozi kozvelemeny elott" kitetel kemeny dolog, na mikor is fog a New York Times-ban felbukkanni, hogy ki felelos a koalicio felbomlasaert?]  Kezdemenyezeseimet az vezerli, hogy a Magyar Koztarsasagban minden korulmenyek kozott ervenyesulnie kell a jognak es az igazsagnak. Ezaltal konnyithetunk az allam polgarainak terhein, ekkent valosithatjuk meg a kozteherviselest, igy erosithetjuk meg a nemzet tekintelyet.Nem engedhetjuk meg a korrupcio elburjanzasat, a visszaelesek ternyereset, a jogtalan vagyonszerzest es vagyongyarapodast. Nem nezhetjuk tetlenul, hogy egyesek buntetlenul karokat okoznak az allampolgaroknak, a becsuletes vallalkozoknak, az onkormanyzatok-nak, a koznek. Kotelessegunk ervenyt szerezni a jog es a tisztesseg normainak. [Ez egy uzenet az allampolgaroknak: "Feher lovon vonulok, ERTETEK. Ertitek? - Kar, hogy a "Nyilatkozat" tovabbi reszei teljesen diszkreditaljak ezt a "moral high ground"-ot]Az allam alkotmanyos feladata gondoskodni polgarainak elet- es vagyonbiztonsagarol, a jogbiztonsagrol. Ennek ervenyre juttatasat fogalmaztuk meg a kormanyprogramban is. Kotelezettseget vallaltunk arra, hogy a tarsadalomra kulonosen veszelyes buncselekmenyekkel szemben a hatekonyabb fellepeshez megteremtjuk a megfelelo jogszabalyi felteteleket, es kialakitjuk a felderites hatekonyabb modszereit.Magyarorszag miniszterelnokekent ahogy eddig, a jovoben is hatarozottan fellepek a korrupcio, a visszaelesek, a gazdasagi buncselekmenyek felderitese, a kozelet tisztasaga erdekeben. Az orszag tekintelyet az eltussolt es nem a feltart visszaelesek jaratjak le. Elfogadhatatlan, hogy egyes gazdasagi csoportok az igazsag-szolgaltatas lassusagaval es a hatosagok erelytelensegevel szamolhassanak. Elfogadhatatlan, hogy tisztesseges allampolgarok a joggal visszaelok kiszolgaltatottjaiva valjanak. [Ez egy kis uzenet a Vilagnak: "Uraim, olvastatok a La Repubblica- ban, hogy nalunk Kleptokracia van, az "evszazad rablasa". Ezert en vagyok a felelos, a Miniszterelnok. Ez az adu asz a kezemben, mostani lepesem nemzetkozi igazolasara]Kormanyzasunk eddigi idoszakaban uj jogszabalyokat alkottunk, meglevoket modositottunk, szervezeti intezkedeseket tettunk, noveltuk a bunuldozo szervek letszamat es penzugyi tamogatasat. Ez lehetove tette az elorelepest a buncselekmenyek felderiteseben es a bunmegelozes teren. [Ezt persze forditva kell olvasni: "Oriasi visszalepes tortent a buncselekmenyek felderiteseben es a bunmegelozes teren" - ujabb onigazolas hogy valamit tenni kell]Az allam megsem tudott kelloen felkeszulni a gazdasagi visszaelesek es a szervezett bunozes terjedese elleni kuzdelemre. Marpedig, ha nem lepunk fel minden lehetseges torvenyes eszkozzel e folyamat ellen, akkor meg sulyosabb karok erhetik a tarsadalmat. Kialakulhat annak a veszelye is, hogy a sokmilliardos visszaelesekre kepes szervezett bunozes a torvenytelenul szerzett jovedelmebol kiterjeszti befolyasat a kozintezmenyekre is. Kepesse valhat kozeleti emberek, tajekoztatasi es mas eszkozok megvasarlasara. A szervezett bunozes sulyosan fenyegeti tarsadalmi ertekeinket. [Ezeket nem "veszelykent", hanem maris vegbement, sot nemzetkozi testuletek altal "kalibralt" folyamatokkent kell erteni. "Tajekoztatasi eszkozok megvasarlasa" kettos utalas egyreszt a Fenyo-Vico sajtobotranyra, masreszt a Freedom House jelentesere, hogy a magyar sajto reszben (azota mar reszben sem) szabad - sajtoszabadsaga Szenegal szintje alatt van, Mongoliaval azonos szinten]A szervezett bunozes visszaszoritasara szeles korben kell tovabbi intezkedeseket tenni. Ennek kereteben a kormany iranyitasa alatt allo, hatekony, gyorsan bevetheto, kulonleges szervezetnek fontos szerepe lehet. A Kozponti Nyomozohivatal betoltheti ezt a feladatkort. Szandekom szerint kormanyszervkent mukodik, torvenyessegi felugyeletet a Legfobb Ugyeszseg gyakorolja. Tevekenyseget az Orszaggyules barmikor ellenorizheti.  [Itt van a Pick Asz; ugy hivjak hogy Kozponti Nyomozohivatal, amerikaiul FBI, ne ugraljon a New York Times, mert nektek is van, regota. Ebben is fedezve vagyok]Elismeres es megbecsules illeti a bunuldozo szervek munkatarsait eddigi erofesziteseikert. Tudataban vagyok annak, hogy felelos munkajukat nagyon nehez korulmenyek kozott vegzik, es a kormany eddigi intezkedesei ellenere meg mindig hianyoznak a szukseges feltetelek. Ezek megteremtese erdekeben tovabbi lepeseket teszunk. A szervezett bunozes elleni fellepes ugyanakkor az eddigieknel hatekonyabb osszefogast, kozos munkat igenyel minden erintett hatosagtol. A tarsadalommal egyutt magam is fokozott figyelemmel kiserem, ahogy az ugyeszek es a birak aktivan kozremukodnek a szervezett bunozes visszaszoritasaban, a magyar igazsagszolgaltatas hatekonysaganak erositeseben es a jog ervenyesulesenek teljesebbe teteleben. [Uzenetek az "apparatusnak": elftarskaim, ezek ujabb munkalehetosegek, a belugyi apparatusnak mostantol ket piaca van, csak oruljetek neki, velem vagytok]Meggyozodesem, hogy nem keslekedhetunk. Ennek indoklasara is szantam ezt a nyilatkozatot. Vallom, hogy a jog es az erkolcs ervenyesitese nem aldozhato fel rosszul ertelmezett partpolitikai erdekek oltaran. A nemzet ugyerol van szo (NSZ). ["Nem keslekedhetunk" azt jelenti, hogy most nem fogok ideiglenesen visszatancolni, mint multkor nassanyival. A "Rosszul ertelmezett partpolitikai erdekek" kodszo kimondja, hogy az SZDSZ a hibas, az ok, az egeszert. "A nemzet ugyerol van szo" nagyjelentosegu kifejezes kimondja, hogy az SZDSZ egy nemzetellenes banda, itt az ideje hogy a nemzet egysegesen forduljon ellene!]* PETO NYILATKOZAT [Na, nezzuk csak hogy viszont Peto milyen nyilatkozatot tett kozze, ugyancsak a szombati Nepszabadsagban]Peto, Kuncze: Mindenben egyetertunk, kiveve a nyomozohivatalt [Roviden, magyarul: en nem akarok valni, ez egy jo hazassag, de ne hozd haza a kurvaidat]Nem fenyeget a koalicio szetesese a kozponti nyomozohivatal korul kialakult vita nyoman - jelentette ki tegnap [penteken] egy veszpremi sajtotajekoztaton Peto Ivan, az SZDSZ elnoke.["a nem fenyeget a szeteses" nem csak azt jelenti, hogy Petoek szandeka a hatalomban maradas (mikor volt ezek celja egyeb, mint a hatalom es az akar tisztessegtelenul is megszerzett penz?), de annak is fenyegeto bejelentese, hogy Peto szerint a valsagbol (megint!) Horn fog veszteskent kijonni!]Az SZDSZ elnoke kijelentette: egyetert a miniszterelnokkel abban, hogy a szervezett bunozes kepes lehet befolyasat a kozintezmeny-ekre is kiterjeszteni. [Magyarul: Hat persze hogy a maffia nyakig benne van a politikaban, de ebben ti MSZP-sek, ugyanolyan sarosak vagytok, mint mi!] Az SZDSZ azonban - ellentetben a miniszterelnok-kel - tovabbra is igy gondolja, hogy ennek megakadalyozasara nem kell nyomozohivatalt folallitani, inkabb a mar meglevo hatosagi intezmenyeket kellene erositeni. [Ez valoban "High Noon"; mi sem fogunk visszalepni allaspontukkal, hogy mi kaptuk a Belugyet, a zsarolas a mi reszortunk!] Szorgalmazta a parlamenti, onkormanyzati es koztisztviseloi osszeferhetetlensegi torvenyek mielobbi megalkotasat [Ha barmi "puhasag" van a nyilatkozatban, ez az: "Ne a gyerek elott a kormanyban veszekedjunk, oldjuk meg ezt a Parlamentben, ahol Ti vagytok tobbsegben (mi meg ugysem tartjuk be a torvenyeket, ha- ha-ha!)]Kozolte: a nyomozohivatal folallitasa koruli vita nem vezethet koalicios valsaghoz. Szerinte az SZDSZ es az MSZP tagjainak tobbsege ragaszkodik a koaliciohoz. A KET-nek ezt is figyelembe kell vennie, amikor a nyomozohivatal ugyerol tanacskozik - mondotta. Felhivta a figyelmet arra, hogy az MSZP vezeto testuletei mindeddig nem nyilvanitottak velemenyt az ugyben. A vita a miniszterelnok es Kuncze Gabor belugyminiszter, valamint a mogotte allo SZDSZ kozott zajlik. [Na, ez a bekezdes megmondja a magaet! Peto szerint az hogy a kormanyban Horn & Kuncze parbaja folyik nem jelent semmit, mert szereny velemenye szerint az SZDSZ, AZ MSZP-BE BEEPITETT MAMELUKOK SEGITSEGEVEL tobbsegben van, es nem hogy a koalicio nem fog szetesni, de HORN FOG KISZORULNI A KEPVISELOKENT VALO SZAVAZAS EREDMENYEKENT! ]* MADARAK: Minden idok egyik legcinikusabb, legmocskosabb ujsagiroi kita'lala'sa [ugyancsak szombati Nepszabadsagbol, Aczel Endre irasa]MADARAK[Aczle Endre, Nepszabadsag, majus 18]Horn Gyula nyilatkozata kettos uzenet. Az egyik a koalicios partnernek, az SZDSZ-nek szol a hetfon esedekes koalicios egyeztetes elott, a masik a magyar nepnek. [Itt "kisse" teved Aczel ur. Legalabb NEGY uzenet van abban; a fenti ketton tul a harmadik a Nyugatnak (NYT) van cimezve, de a negyedik uzenet, az apparatus elftarsainak, szinten nem elhanyagolhato]Ami az elsot illeti: a szocialista kormanyfo kitart a kozponti nyomozohivatal otlete mellett, nem keri Kuncze Gabor SZDSZ-es miniszterelnok-helyettes es belugyminiszter alternativ otletet. Allaspontja, latszolag, vegleges. [Ez igaz, beallt a "High Noon", nyilvanvalo]. Ami a masodikat illeti: Horn meglehetosen dramai hangon ertesiti a nepet arrol, hogy miert ilyen konok. Szerinte a szervezett bunozes a falakon belul van, a helyzet nem egyszeruen rossz, hanem katasztrofalis. ("A szervezett bunozes sulyosan fenyegeti tarsadalmi ertekeinket.") Ha pedig ilyen, akkor kulonleges lepesek szuksegeltetnek. [Ez is igaz, Horn a Kleptokracia nemzetkozileg elismert tenyevel fedezi SZDSZ-ellenes kiallasat]. Ezt kell minden magyar embernek (minusz SZDSZ) megertenie. [Hopp, itt Aczel ur is uzen a NYT-nak: HORN SZERINT AZ SZDSZ NEM MAGYAR EMBEREKBOL ALL, VAGYIS MOSTANI LEPESET TESSEK SZIVES LENNI ANTIZASNAK KICIKKEZNI. (Ez persze nehez lesz, a Horn-apuka hovatartozasa miatt, de hat ha Zsirinovszkijt lehet ugyanilyen szarmazas ellenere antizni, miert ne lehetne Gyulust?)]A "kulonleges" szot nem en talaltam ki, benne van a nyilatkozatban. A kozponti nyomozohivatal jelzojekent. Nem a legszerencsesebb minosites, mert kinosan emlekeztet a bolsevik forradalom utan, az ellenforradalom megfekezese erdekeben eletre hivott szervezet, a Cseka ("Csrezvucsajnaja Komisszija") megnevezesere, kovetkezeskepp a felelem felkeltesere alkalmas. [Hoho! Huha! Ez am a beszed! Forditas magyarra: "Ha nem lepsz vissza, kiteregetjuk teljes bolsevik multadat!"- mondja a kozmoliberalis sajto. Csak tessek figyelni, kedves olvaso, hogy fognak elokerulni a szajbarugasok, szajbavizeles-ek, Rosztovi es 56-os "kemenymagos bolseviki cselekedetek"!]Mit mondjak, nem szeretem a "kulonleges szervezeteket". Meg akkor sem, ha szuloik a legtisztabb lelekkel allitjak, hogy felni csak a gonoszoknak van okuk, az artatlan nepnek ("allampolgarok, becsuletes vallalkozok, onkormanyzatok, a koz") semmi felnivaloja nincsen es nem is lehet. Csakhogy egy ilyen, a kormany ala rendelt szervezet pillanatokon belul rajon a maga "kulonleges" helyzetere, hogy azt ne mondjam hatalmara, es onnantol kezdve demokracia legyen a talpan az, amelyik meg tudja fekezni. Jobbak a nem kulonleges szervezetek, roluk legalabb tudom, hogy mire kepesek, es mire nem. [Itt a kovetkezo uzenet: SZABADJARA ENGEDJUK A KOZMOLIBERALIS SAJTOT HOGY "DEMOKRACIAELLENESSEGGEL" VADOLJUK HORN-T.  Ejnye, milyen ismeros nemely fenyegetes! Mintha pontosan ugyanezt tette volna az SZDSZ Antallek ellen a "Demokratikus Charta"-val! Csakhogy Konradot most elovenni nem lesz tul celszeru]De ez meg hagyjan. Eddig ugy tudtam, hogy a kozponti nyomozo-hivatal a koznek kirivoan nagy kart okozo gazdasagi buncselek-menyek gyors es hatekony feltarasara lesz hivatott, es pirulva bar, de a korrupciot es az ugynevezett feketegazdasagot tekinti egyik celpontjanak. A Horn-nyilatkozatban ennek nyoma nincsen. Ez a nyilatkozat a kerdes irodalmanak teljesen uj dokumentuma. Ez, szinte kizarolag, csak a szervezett bunozesrol beszel. Amely azonban (szotart hivok segitsegul) fogalmilag alapvetoen a szervezett lopasra, rablasra, az ilyen modon szerzett javak hataron tuli ertekesitesere, a kurvatartasra, valamint az illegalis szerencsejatekokra terjed ki. Van benne meg kis fegyvercsempeszes, tiltott alkohol- es kabitoszer-ertekesites, ilyesmi. [Na, ilyen sem volt mar regesreg. Csak tessek szives lenni magyar forditasban megvizsgalni a szoveget. Ez meglehetosen atlatszo fatyollal Hornekat azzal fenyegeti meg, hogy "A maffiatevekenysegben Ti is benne vagytok, de nyakig! Soroljam csak, mivel fogunk MI elojonni ellenetek? Pici apro lepes innen "szemely(ek)re lebontani" melyik MSZP-s csinal "szervezett lopast", melyik miniszter tart kurvat (nana, hogy kozpenzen, csak nem fogja a felesegetol kerni), ki van benne nyakig az illegalis szerencse-jatekban, fegyvercsempeszesben, alkohol es kabitoszermaffiakban. Ezek mar SZEMELYRE SZOLO leleplezesi fenyegetesek!]Nos akkor: mely neme a szervezett bunozesnek az, amelynek Horn Gyula akar a koalicio felbomlasa aran is kesztyut dob? Hogy egy palyatarsamat idezzem: "en azt nem tudom". Csak remelhetem, hogy a miniszterelnok legalabb a sajat partjat es a sajat kormanyat nem hagyja annyira homalyban, mint engem. [Elore magyar "vizsgalo riporterek": pontositsatok csak a temat, Horn melyik MSZP-s minisztereire gondolt, melyik vadjaval, Aczel Endre?]Az persze egeszen mas kerdes, hogy olajszokitesen, ado- es vamcsalason meg hasonlokon meggazdagodott emberek politikusok es tajekoztatasi eszkozok (lapok, radiok) megvasarlasaval epitgetik tovabb kicsiny birodalmukat. [Hoho! Huha! Je! Nahat! Ez aztan mindenre ratesz egy lapattal! Itt Aczel mar egyenesen Horn-t fenyegeti meg szemelyesen, hogy az Olajgate-szeru botranyokat -melyben az MSZP nyakig benne van- fogjak OK, AZ SZDSZ, KITEREGETNI -- ha muszaj][Ugy gondolja az olvaso, hogy mindez a mocsok, aljas nyilvanos zsarolas, keresztbe zsarolas, belfoldi es kulfoldi fenyegetesozon azert megis tulzas egy kicsit? Na, tessek fogozkodni, ilyen meg nem volt leirva modern ujsagirasban, legalabb is Europaban nem, talan csak Szenegalban (melyet kovetunk) es mas, meg sotetebb helyeken:] Ezek ketsegkivul undorito dolgok, de azert egy gazdasag altalanos egeszseget legfeljebb minimalfokon befolyasoljak. Tanaka Kakuei hajdani japan miniszterelnokot 2,2 millio dollarert vasarolta meg maganak a Lockheed, hogy az o gepeit vegye meg a japan allami legitarsasag, am ettol Japan meg folyamatosan gazdagodott es erosodott. Mas pelda. Az egesz olasz politikai elit korrupt volt, am korruptsaga tetopontjan Italia az egy fore juto GDP-t tekintve eppen megelozte a teljesen korrupciomentes Nagy-Britanniat, es Europa harmadik gazdasagi hatalmava lepett elo. Ugyhogy azt mondanam: Magyarorszagnak biztos sok baja van, de a szerves bajok kozott nem a szervezett bunozes, meg csak nem is a korrupcio a legelso. [Nos, mit tetszenek szolni? Jo, varok, mig levegot tetszenek venni. Nem tevedes, AZ SZDSZ VEDELMEBE VESZI A KLEPTOKRACIA INTEZMENYET. "Uraim, legyunk liberalisak! "Lopni szabad, csak rajt ne kapjanak!"  Sot, a rablas ERENY; attol lesz Japan es Olaszorszag eros, kar hogy a $2.2 millios arfolyamot mieink meg nem ertek el!]A tarsadalom igazsagerzetevel termeszetesen egeszen mas a helyzet. Ha az itteni betegsegeket akarja gyogyitani Horn a maga nyomozoi-val, mint ahogyan utal is ra o "minden korulmenyek kozott ervenyesulnie kell a jognak es az igazsagnak" - , akkor legyen! Csak lehetoleg a kettot ne keverje egymassal. Mert a jognak mindig kotelezo, az igazsagnak viszont legfeljebb kivanatos ervenyt szerezni. Nem beszelve arrol, hogy az igazsagszolgaltatas lassusagat a kozponti nyomozohivatal vegkepp nem lesz kepes orvosolni. Hogy egy eletszeru parhuzammal eljek, Steffi Graf apja sem azert var oszig a perere, mert nem voltak eleg furgek a nyomozok, hanem azert, mert a mannheimi birosag gazdasagi itelotablai (het darab) jovatehetet-lenul "tulterheltek". [Ez egy kicsit komplikaltabb rejtbeszed, de azert lefordithato magyarra. "Gyuluskam, hulye vagy. Hogy kepzeled, hogy a nyomozohivataloddal fogsz leleplezni MINKET? Nyomozas utan az IGAZSAGSZOLGALTATASNAK kell kimondani a donto szot -- itt pedig igazan van eleg eronk arra, hogy legalabbis evekig hatraltassuk az ugyek "kimenetelet". Amig Ti az igazsaguggyel fogtok evekig vacakolni, mi mar HOLNAP (bocs, MAR EZZEL A CIKKEL) leleplezunk titeket az altalunk kontrollalt belfoldi sajtoval es kulfoldon megjelentetett cikkekkel! Gyuluskam, le vagy maradva egy brosuraval, mert meg mindig a Rosztovi tankonyvekbol dolgozol. Sztalin mindent a Csekaval es az Igazsaguggyel csinalt, modern vilagban viszont SAJTOVAL dolgozunk]Meg szimplabb szferakba szallva ala: ertjuk, hogyne ertenenk az SZDSZ aggalyait es vetojat. A Horn-fele "kulonleges" szervezet alkalmas annak a sulyos gyanunak a felkeltesere, hogy a koalicios partner ellenorizte Belugyminiszterium (rendorseg) hataskore csokken, szervei alarendelt szerepbe jutnak. (Probalta volna valaki a hajdani koalicios idokben a kommunista belugyminiszter (Rajk) jogositvanyait megnyirbalni! Az megnezhette magat.) [Na, ez mar egyenes beszed, nincs itt semmi jelbeszed, kodos utalas, testcsel. Ez mar a brutalis valosag, hogy a temanak semmi mashoz nincs koze ("szakmai vita?" ha-ha-ha!), csakis az SZDSZ "reszortjaba" adott nyomozati monopolum MSZP-feltorese a tet. Az sem jelbeszed, hogy ugyanez ment vegbe Rajkkal, kicsit korabban, sot azt is tudja mindenki, hogy ebbe a menetbe bele lehet halni, pl. Rajk is belehalt mar.  Horn igy ketszeresen nem lesz elso, tortenelemben mar regen mindig igy volt, a repedes a SAJAT nyakcsigolyajan szinten mutatja hogy a tortenelem szokta ismetelni onmagat.]Ezert vedi Kuncze es partja a szo szoros ertelmeben a mundert, es talan ezert is ov attol a jovotol, ahol nyomozati ugyekben elkerul-hetetlenul is ket rivalis, hangsulyozom: rivalis szervezet nezne egymassal szembe. Egy szocialista (a kozponti nyomozohivatal), meg egy SZDSZ-es (rendorseg) alarendeltsegu, mindketto versenyhelyzet-ben. Es mindketto akkor erezne jol magat, ha a masik "madarai" kozul tudna leszedni egy-kettot.  [Egyenes beszed: ket rivalis allig felfegyverzett rablobanda fog nyiltszini harcot folytatni Budapest utcain, melynek elso aldozatai eppen azok a maffiafonokok lesznek, akiket "keresztbe lepleznek le" a rivalis nyomozohivatalok.][Na, most vegul megtudjuk, mit is jelent az SZDSZ cimere. A most kovetkezo sornal aljasabb, cinikusabb, nyiltabb bunozoi felhivas meg nem iratott le (volt) kulturallamban:]Nem jobb igy, hogy a madarak sertetlenul szarnyalnak?[Magyarul: Gyula, gondold meg. Ma meg visszalephetsz, es akkor folytathatjuk a szabadrablast. Ha pedig nem visszakozol, madarakat le szoktak loni]=LEVEL - VITADate: Fri, 17 May 96 23:44:31 -0700From: WHTSOCIETY <cartrdge@primenet.com>To: signed.nemzet@magyar.siliconvalley.comSubject: Koszonet...Koszonet a munkaert urak es holgyek.=LA'BHOZ!(Magyar Forum, majus 9.)Jelentkezett az Uj Magyarorszag szerkesztosegeben az a fiatal tanarember, aki a kozelmultban fekete festekkel leontotte a szigetvari Szulajman-szobrot. Egyebek mellett a kovetkezoket mondta: "Magyar emberkent megalazonak talaltam, hogy egy bennunket leigazo embernek ilyen monumentalis alkotastengedelyeztek felallitani... A magyarsag meggyalazasanak tartom, hogy ezt a szobrot ide, Szigetvarra felallitottak. Olyan ez, mintha Augsburgban Lehel vezernek mi keszitenenk dicsoito szobrot... Erdekes, amikor a cegledi Kossuth-szobor kardjat letortek, amikor Szuz Maria szobrat ledontottek, alig kapott visszhangot. De mert en... a magyarsag ontudatat sarba tipro alkotast bemocskoltam... a rendorseg ugymond hajtovadaszatot inditott kezrekeritesemre..."Tenyleg fiatalemberrol lehet szo, hiszen nem tudja, hogy ebben az orszagban mekkora multjuk van mar a nemzeti ontudatot letipro szobroknak. Nehany eve, evtizede meg szinte sorjaztak a Sztalin-, a Lenin- es a hosszovjetkatona-alkotasok az orszagban, valamirevalo varost el sem lehetett kepzelni "felszabadulasi" obeliszk nelkul. Ma is van meg beloluk.A Szulejman-szobor is a megalazkodas termeke. Mint felallitasakor elmondtak, "diplomaciai" okokbol volt szukseg a felallitasara. Mert elso a diplomacia, csak az utan jon a nemzet meg a nemzeti onerzet...Szigetvartol nem messze, Taszaron kulonben cipopucolo embereket keres az ott allomasozo amerikai katonasag. Jo penzt adnak, csak egy kicsit faraszto a poz. Leterdelni, meggorbedni...Pilah Gyorgy=OMRI RUSSIAN PRESIDENTIAL ELECTION SURVEY No. 3, 16 MAY 1996CANDIDATES AND PARTIESLAST POSSIBLE CANDIDATE REJECTED. The last presidential candidate hoping to join the 11 contenders registered for the June election failed to win his Supreme Court appeal. On 12 May, the court ruled that the Central Electoral Commission's (TsIK) refusal to register Moscow Investment Fund President Vyacheslav Ushakov was legitimate, Russian media reported. Ushakov was rejected for failing to obtain 1 million valid signatures; forged signatures were found on his petition. Earlier, four other potential candidates for the presidential race were rejected for the same reason (see OMRI Special Report, no. 2). -- Anna ParetskayaZYUGANOV OUTLINES HIS PROGRAM FOR THE ECONOMY . . . In a 12 May interview with the Russian TV (RTR) weekly analytical program "Zerkalo," Communist Party (KPRF) leader and presidential candidate Gennadii Zyuganov revealed the main points of his economic program. Although the free market is "a natural and normal phenomenon" that is 7,000 years old, an unregulated market is unsuitable for Russia, he argued. Zyuganov added that he supports various forms of property ownership, including private, although he said he gives priority to the "public property forms" that take into consideration Russia's "national character." He said the state should own a controlling share in various sectors of the economy, including energy, transport, military industry, education, and science. However, Zyuganov declared that there will be no forced renationalization, and only loss-making enterprises may have their privatization reversed. Nevertheless, during a recent campaign swing through St. Petersburg, Zyuganov said he agrees with scholars who say the optimum balance of state and private property in an economy is 61% to 39%, respectively. -- Anna Paretskaya. . . AND DEFENDING RUSSIAN CULTURE. Meanwhile, in an interview with the opposition weekly Zavtra (no. 17), Zyuganov declared that national culture and morals are being deliberately destroyed in Russia. He advocated more funding for and state control over the development of Russian culture, and proposed introducing censorship of films, books, and advertisements imported from abroad. In addition, Zyuganov argued that a "public council" for television should be instituted, which would consist of prominent scholars, writers, and priests. The council would oversee television schedules and reduce the number of programs featuring money, murders, and pornography, which Zyuganov said are the only things currently shown on television. Speaking about the enormous role of the Russian Orthodox Church in Russian culture and politics, Zyuganov advocated placing restrictions on foreign religious groups, which he said are encouraged by the current authorities. -- Anna ParetskayaCOMMUNIST FOREIGN POLICY DIFFERS LITTLE FROM YELTSIN'S? Zyuganov's aides are preparing a report outlining the basic principles on which the Communist leader's foreign policy would be based if he were elected, perhaps in order to differentiate their candidate from President Yeltsin. But a recent interview in the weekly Vek (no. 18) with one of the authors of the document, Aleksei Podberezkin, instead reflected the similarities in the two leading contenders' foreign policy positions. Podberezkin, currently deputy chairman of the Duma International Affairs Committee, said Zyuganov's foreign policy would aim to defend Russia's "core national interests," and focus on the former Soviet republics. When pressed to explain how this stance differentiated Zyuganov from Yeltsin, however, he simply asserted that Zyuganov had advocated such a policy since 1989, while for others it was merely a "loud declaration." Podberezkin later conceded that Yeltsin had already co-opted much of Zyuganov's foreign policy program, especially with regard to accelerating CIS integration. He nonetheless argued that substantial differences still separate the two candidates. Zyuganov would more "categorically" oppose NATO expansion, even further accelerate CIS integration, and more rapidly restore ties with former Soviet allies. Vek speculated that foreign policy is not playing a major role in the campaign precisely because the differences between Yeltsin and his opponents are relatively small. -- Scott ParrishFORMER LDPR MEMBER EXPOSES PARTY. Duma Deputy Aleksandr Vengerovskii claimed in an interview with Izvestiya on 13 May that half of the Duma deputies representing Vladimir Zhirinovsky's Liberal Democratic Party of Russia (LDPR) bought their places on the party list for an average of $1 million. Vengerovskii was number two on the LDPR list for the December parliamentary election. He quit the party in March due to "circumstances known to the LDPR chairman" but did not further elaborate. He told Izvestiya that the Duma faction's readiness to sell spots on the party list and lobby for the interests of those who could pay had led to strong connections between the LDPR and criminal groups from Moscow, St. Petersburg, and Lipetsk. According to Vengerovskii, the LDPR only developed a central and regional structure after its strong showing in the 1993 parliamentary election. Winning representation in the Duma entitled the party to state financing for its apparatus. Moreover, Vengerovskii questioned the truthfulness of the income declaration that Zhirinovsky recently submitted to the Central Electoral Commission along with other registration documents. According to the declaration, Zhirinovsky's income in 1996 was 29 million rubles (about $5,800), but Vengerovskii claimed that Zhirinovsky owned all LDPR property. Zhirinovsky described the interview as a provocation, telling Ekho Moskvy on 13 May that Vengerovskii had been drugged and was completely motionless, deaf, and blind during the interview. Vengerovskii has stood by his comments. -- Anna ParetskayaZHIRINOVSKY CALLS FOR RETURN OF TSAR. Liberal Democratic Party of Russia leader Vladimir Zhirinovsky said in his first campaign speech carried by Radio Mayak on 14 May that Russia needs an "emperor . . . a president with huge powers similar to those of the tsars or of [Communist Party] general secretaries," Reuters reported. "Russia is an empire. It cannot be a humiliated republic with a rotten democracy, a declining economy, and a weak army," he said. In January, Zhirinovsky marked his 25th wedding anniversary with an elaborate second marriage ceremony in a Moscow cathedral. The celebration included tsarist-era rituals; the couple arrived in a horse-drawn troika as Zhirinovsky threw money to well-wishers and curious onlookers. -- Robert OrttungMORE SUPPORT FOR YELTSIN. Duma deputy Boris Gromov, a popular retired army colonel general, accompanied President Yeltsin on his recent campaign trip to the Volga region and urged all democratic candidates and parties to back Yeltsin in June, RTR and AFP reported on 13 May. In early 1995, Gromov was transferred from the post of deputy defense minister to the Foreign Ministry; he had publicly criticized the military operation in Chechnya. He subsequently led the opposition electoral bloc My Fatherland in the December parliamentary election. Meanwhile, on a visit to the Komi Republic, Russian Orthodox Church Patriarch Aleksii II urged voters "to make the right choice" and prevent the Communists from returning to power, according to Kommersant-Daily on 14 May. -- Anna ParetskayaINDUSTRIALIST LEADER BACKS YELTSIN. The leader of the Russian Union of Industrialists and Entrepreneurs, Arkadii Volskii, said in an interview with Izvestiya on 13 May that he will support President Yeltsin in next month's election. Volskii added that he would have preferred that the election be postponed. He criticized Yeltsin for "destroying the old house before building a new one . . . one could have sheltered in the old house from the rain." He also protested the fining of directors who paid wages late, saying that delays in federal payments were often to blame. On 14 May, Volskii's union held its 7th congress in Moscow. -- Peter RutlandPRIVATE FARMERS SUPPORT YELTSIN. . . Meeting in Moscow on 14 May, the second congress of the Union of Landowners called on rural dwellers to vote for President Yeltsin, Russian media reported. The union supports agricultural reform, in particular the right to private ownership of farmland. In March, Yeltsin issued a decree allowing the buying and selling of farmland, a move that delighted groups like the Union of Landowners but enraged the anti-reform Agrarian Party of Russia (APR). Deputy Prime Minister Aleksandr Zaveryukha was forced to resign his APR membership for his part in drafting and implementing the decree. -- Laura Belin. . .WHILE AGRARIANS STAND BEHIND ZYUGANOV. The Agrarian Party of Russia (APR) outlined "instructions" for its preferred presidential candidate, Gennadii Zyuganov, in the April issue of Rossiiskaya zemlya. The APR called for prohibiting the buying and selling of farmland, instituting price controls on agricultural products, and maintaining Russia's "food security" by banning the "dumping" of imported foods. Zyuganov has named Vasilii Starodubtsev, the APR's number three candidate for the December parliamentary election, to his "shadow cabinet." Starodubtsev helped organize the August 1991 coup; he now leads the Agrarian Union and is chairman of the "Lenin" collective farm in Tula Oblast, described by admirers as a "little island of socialism." In an April interview with Narodnaya pravda, Starodubtsev said that if he were appointed agriculture minister, he would establish parity between what farmers must pay for agricultural inputs, such as fuel and fertilizer, and the prices they receive for their produce. He would also favor domestic agricultural producers. Echoing Zyuganov's campaign rhetoric, which separates ordinary Soviet-era communists from a long-standing "party of betrayal," Starodubtsev asserted that "Bukharin, Trotsky, Zinoviev, Kamenev, Khrushchev, Gorbachev, and others," including current cabinet members, were oriented toward the West and hated the Russian countryside. -- Laura BelinCANDIDATES CONSIDER RESTORING VICE PRESIDENCY. Aleksandr Lebed has become the latest candidate to call for re-creating the vice presidency in Russia, Nezavisimaya gazeta reported on 14 May. Zyuganov earlier suggested that he would name Aman Tuleev as his vice president if elected. President Yeltsin is thought to be considering naming Federation Council Chairman Yegor Stroev to this position since he would be very helpful in drawing regional support.         Mikhail Gorbachev first instituted the position in 1991, when he appointed Gennadii Yanaev USSR vice president. Yanaev joined his boss's opponents in trying to remove him in August of that year. Yeltsin dismissed Russia's first vice president, Aleksandr Rutskoi, who had sided with Ruslan Khasbulatov's parliament against the president in 1993. Yeltsin then abolished the position when writing the constitution approved in the referendum of 1993. In his recent statement, Lebed argued that two divorces does not mean that one should do away with the institution of marriage.         There are a number of incentives for trying to restore the office. The position is useful as a reward for partners in political coalitions. Since it is mainly ceremonial, it could also be an effective way of removing a rival from within one's own camp. However, the actual creation of the post will have to wait until after the elections when the constitution can be changed. Getting an amendment approved would be easier for Zyuganov than Yeltsin, since left-wing deputies have a working majority in the Duma. -- Robert OrttungMAIN TV NETWORKS OFFER SKEPTICAL VIEW OF ZYUGANOV. The Moscow-based media is predominantly anti-Communist, fearing a crackdown if Gennadii Zyuganov is elected president, and this orientation was noticeable in television coverage of Zyuganov's recent campaign trip to Nizhnii Novgorod. A Russian Public TV (ORT) news report on 12 May included this commentary:"Today in Nizhnii Novgorod, where Zyuganov was making a campaign visit, it was revealed that the publication of the final program of the Communist bloc has been postponed again. There's a coalition for you. All the participants need to approve the program. But in so far as different types of politicians are assembled [in Zyuganov's coalition], from Bolsheviks to social democrats, it's not surprising that the program will not be settled soon, maybe only right before 16 June. Again, if you think logically, a program should of course be ready beforehand. But on the other hand, according to a candidate's logic, the later it appears, the less time competitors will have to rip it to shreds."The ORT commentator did not mention that President Yeltsin has yet to unveil his own election platform; its release was postponed from March to April and is now scheduled for late May. RTR on 12 May mentioned that only about 400 elderly supporters turned up for a pro-Zyuganov rally in Nizhnii Novgorod. Like ORT, RTR emphasized that Zyuganov has yet to explain exactly how he would improve the country's economy if he is elected. Meanwhile, on the same day, the private network NTV also commented that Zyuganov has not revealed his economic platform, without mentioning that Yeltsin has yet to release his own program. The pro- Communist newspaper Pravda complained on 14 May that the media have paid insufficient attention to Zyuganov's campaign trips. The paper also asserted that Zyuganov has little in common with the non-charismatic image "democratic" journalists have created for him. -- Laura BelinORT ELECTION ANALYSIS FAVORS YELTSIN. The 11 May edition of the ORT current events program "19:59" reflected the editorial bias typical of election coverage on Channel 1. Following a segment on Aleksandr Lebed's strengths and weaknesses as a presidential candidate, one expert from the polling firm Vox Populi argued that the best strategy for Lebed and other "third force" candidates would be not to compete against President Yeltsin and to encourage their supporters to back him. Another commentator asserted that in today's environment "there is no choice, only Yeltsin." He admitted that Yeltsin was a "partocrat" during the Soviet era but argued that he has demonstrated his commitment to perestroika, "body and soul." Furthermore, changing presidents now could provoke "carnage" in Russia. On 13 May, ITAR-TASS reported that "19:59" would be canceled due to low ratings and practically unanimous criticism in the press. -- Laura BelinRUSSIAN REGIONS WILL BACK YELTSIN. By late-April opinion polls showed that Zyuganov's support had leveled off while President Yeltsin continued to gain backers. Yeltsin's strength lies in his support from the regions outside of Moscow which, in spite of their wide diversity, have a common interest in backing the incumbent because, during the years of reform (no matter how one views them) the regions received considerable autonomy from the center, the St. Petersburg paper Na smenu! argued on 18 April. The regions have become used to setting their own prices on goods and services and determining how much social support they should give to the needy, even if they received these rights only recently, and they would be unwilling to give them up, the paper asserted. Regional elites believe that the Communists only support the idea of federalism in their rhetoric and would re-establish an army of Moscow bureaucrats to control the minutiae of provincial life if they returned to power. The Communist program envisions boosting industrial production and agriculture, while raising wages and pensions. Since the federal budget does not have the funds to carry out these programs, the Communists would have to squeeze resources from beyond Moscow's ring road. One mechanism they could use to exert control over regional resources would be to give greater powers to the presidential representatives in the regions. The current representatives have little influence over local leaders, but their position would be greatly strengthened if, for example, they were in charge of distributing federal resources locally. The regional leaders see Yeltsin as  more inclined to ensure their autonomy and are willing to work with him. Even the "red" governors are coming closer to Yeltsin in order to maintain their autonomy, the article asserts. -- Robert OrttungRUSSIAN QUESTION PLAYS SMALL ROLE IN PRESIDENTIAL CAMPAIGN. There is little room for Zyuganov and Zhirinovsky to increase their electoral base by using nationalist appeals, because this issue is not very salient for undecided voters, who are anyway more likely to identify with the positions of Yeltsin and Yavlinskii on these issues, according to a report based on data about ethnic Russians collected by the Public Opinion Foundation published in Polis (no. 1). Only an incident like the June 1995 crisis in Budennovsk, when Chechen fighters took more than 1,000 hostages at a Russian hospital, could make Russians believe they or their families are under threat from another ethnic group. Otherwise, ethnic issues will play a small role in the campaign, the report concluded. The report said Zhirinovsky's supporters politicize questions of ethnicity more than do those who back other candidates. For example, they are more interested in raising the status of Russians at home and annexing foreign territories that have a large Russian population. The report argued that the nationalism of Zyuganov's supporters is essentially a "holdover of Soviet mass consciousness" based on the idea of "socialist internationalism" that allowed Russians to "feel they belonged to an ethnic majority, supported their imperial consciousness, and justified their right to be called 'older brothers.' " Consequently, attitudes about identity do not have much political significance among the communist supporters. -- Robert OrttungZHIRINOVSKY VIEWED AS THE "REAL THIRD FORCE." The "real third force" candidate who could edge out President Yeltsin and advance to the second round is not Grigorii Yavlinskii, but Vladimir Zhirinovsky, according to Segodnya on 13 May. The author noted that in the 1991 presidential election, as well as the election to the Duma in 1993 and 1995, Zhirinovsky received about twice as many votes as opinion polls had predicted. In fact, since personality plays a larger role in the presidential election than in the parliamentary vote, Zhirinovsky could very well improve on the 11% his Liberal Democratic Party of Russia received in December 1995. His effective television presence may prove crucial in the race. If Yavlinskii insists on running for president independently rather than making a deal with Yeltsin, Segodnya argued, the "nightmarish prospects" for a second-round battle between Zhirinovsky and Zyuganov could become a reality. -- Laura BelinThis material was reprinted with permission of the Open Media  Research Institute, a nonprofit organization with research offices in  Prague, Czech Republic. For more information on OMRI publications,  please write to:  info@omri.czftp://ftp.ifi.uio.no/pub/pgp-----BEGIN PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK-----Version: 2.2mQCNAjCa/14AAAEEALKTqTI1BVtFs63+rV0zPyTQZ3Mi0iNPrFK0SJw71ypW0QM+medOV8X0UZaeKYg455IdB9QfC7tEi7xWZGPSiGbUxlhuN4hTOonFhIRJg2CDE3iG53OSsh2OHRyM3O0ozTnroKKoFax8Wz9wZQsrNQc5fpbx/JFqG43bm6trFGRjAAURtChOZW16ZXQgPG5lbXpldEBtYWd5YXIuc2lsaWNvbnZhbGxleS5jb20+=WggG-----END PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK-----
